---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Training — Your Team Learns Our System."
  description="An Avorix chef with sous chef experience documents your menu, sets it up in the Cook App, and trains your team — directly at the stove, not in a seminar room."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-28 pb-16 px-6 bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50/50 to-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-brand-100 text-brand-700 text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full mb-6">
        Module: The Training
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6 leading-tight">
        Your Team Learns Our System.<br />From Chefs Who Can Do It Themselves.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-10">
        An Avorix chef with at least sous chef experience documents your menu, sets it up in the Cook App, and trains your team — directly at the stove, not in a seminar room.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/en/contact"
        data-cta-location="schulung-hero"
        class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors"
      >
        Book a Demo
      </a>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-neutral-100 px-4 py-2 rounded-full">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-brand-500 shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
        </svg>
        Official staff leasing permit (Federal Employment Agency)
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Two Paths -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 border-t border-neutral-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 text-center mb-12">
        Training That Fits Your Business.
      </h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- Path 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-neutral-200 hover:border-brand-200 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-brand-600 font-bold text-sm">1</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Path 1: Block Training</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
            Five days with six hours each, focused entirely on training. Typically two blocks: in the first block, the Avorix chef documents your menu and sets up the recipes in the app. In the second block, your team works through the dishes until every step is second nature.
          </p>
        </div>
        <!-- Path 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-neutral-200 hover:border-brand-200 hover:shadow-md transition-all">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-100 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-brand-600 font-bold text-sm">2</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Path 2: Live Training</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
            The Avorix chef works normally in your kitchen and trains your team alongside operations. The running business is not interrupted, and yet know-how grows shift by shift. Especially suited when you cannot free up days for pure training.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 text-center mt-8 bg-brand-50 rounded-xl px-6 py-3">
        For both paths: the Avorix chef has at least sous chef experience.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- At the Stove -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">
        At the Stove. In Real Operations. With Your Own Food.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Our chef doesn't train with example recipes from a manual. They take your menu, build the recipes in the Cook App, and work through them with your team — with the ingredients you have in house, on the equipment in your kitchen. The result: after training, your team can cook exactly the dishes your guests order.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        If you're short on staff during the training phase, we can provide additional chefs through our staff module so operations continue while your team learns.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/en/staff"
        data-cta-location="schulung-personal-link"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-brand-500 font-semibold hover:text-brand-600 transition-colors"
      >
        To the Staff Module
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">What Does It Cost?</h2>
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-neutral-200">
        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Clear hourly rates and block prices, no hidden fees. You get the numbers in black and white during the first call. For the first businesses, there are pilot conditions in 2026 significantly below the regular price.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/en/contact"
          data-cta-location="schulung-kosten"
          class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors"
        >
          Book a Demo
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-neutral-50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-10 text-center">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 bg-white group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            Who are the chefs that train at our location?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            All Avorix training chefs have at least sous chef experience in upscale hotels or restaurants. They know the Avorix system because they work with it themselves, and they know how to lead a kitchen team.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 bg-white group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            What if the chef doesn't fit our team?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Then we swap them out. The chemistry between training chef and kitchen team has to be right, otherwise the training doesn't work. Let us know, and we'll send a different chef.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 bg-white group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            How quickly will my team be ready?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            That depends on the size of your menu and your team's experience level. Typically two training blocks of five days each. After that, your team can cook the dishes independently with the app. With live training it takes a bit longer, but operations continue uninterrupted.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-4 bg-white group">
          <summary class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between">
            Do the chefs work with the Cook App?
            <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mt-3 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. The training chef sets up your recipes in the Avorix Cook App and shows your team how to work with it. After training, your team has the app with all recipes, photos, and step-by-step instructions on the tablet in the kitchen.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">
        Tell Us What Your Kitchen Needs.
      </h2>
      <a
        href="/en/contact"
        data-cta-location="schulung-final"
        class="inline-block bg-brand-500 text-white px-10 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-base hover:bg-brand-600 transition-colors shadow-lg shadow-brand-200"
      >
        Book a Demo
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
